article.headline: Tennessee St. 80, Jacksonville St. 70
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Ala. -- Gerald Robinson scored 23 points to lead Tennessee State to an 80-70 win over Jacksonville State on Monday night. Jerrell Houston added 19 points for the Tigers (7-17, 5-9 Ohio Valley Conference), who snapped a five game losing streak with the victory. Tennessee State broke a 46-46 tie with a 7-0 run that was capped by a Parker Smith jumper with 10:28 remaining in the second half. A 6-1 spurt later in the half put the Tigers up by 12 points, 71-59, with 4:06 left in the game. Jacksonville State failed to get closer than six points the rest of the way. The Gamecocks (11-12, 5-9) were led by Brandon Crawford, who finished with 14 points and nine rebounds. Jonathan Toles added 12 points and seven assists for Jacksonville State. The Tigers shot 58.5 percent from the field (31-for-53).
